{"id":"305636040_Hyperbolic_Systems_of_Balance_Laws","abstract":"In this chapter we provide an introduction to the modeling of balance laws\nby hyperbolic partial differential equations (PDEs). A balance law is the mathematical expression of the physical principle that the variation of the amount of some extensive quantity over a bounded domain is balanced by its flux through the boundaries of the domain and its production/consumption inside the domain. Balance laws are therefore used to represent the fundamental dynamics of many physical open conservative systems.","authors":["Georges Bastin","Jean-Michel Coron"],"meta":["July 2016","DOI:10.1007/978-3-319-32062-5_1","In book: Stability and Boundary Stabilization of 1-D Hyperbolic Systems (pp.1-54)"],"references":["287576912_Moving_horizon_estimation_in_managed_pressure_drilling_using_distributed_models","280036232_Well-posedness_and_exact_controllability_of_the_mass_balance_equations_for_an_extrusion_process","275722935_Stationary_states_in_gas_networks","271771309_Feedback_Stabilization_for_the_Mass_Balance_Equations_of_an_Extrusion_Process","267015618_Classical_Solutions_in_Sobolev_Spaces_for_a_Class_of_Hyperbolic_Lotka--Volterra_Systems","265662549_General_constrained_conservation_laws_Application_to_pedestrian_flow_modeling","243101659_Kinetic_and_Fluid_Model_Hierarchies_for_Supply_Chains","235326469_Output_Feedback_Stabilization_for_a_Scalar_Conservation_Law_with_a_Nonlocal_Velocity","233564624_An_Acoustic_Model_for_Automatic_Control_of_a_Slide_Flute","230788763_A_2D_model_for_hydrodynamics_and_biology_coupling_applied_to_algae_growth_simulations","230653481_Prion_dynamic_with_size_dependency-strain_phenomena","228671740_A_continuous_model_for_supply_chains_with_finite_buffers","313202993_Theorie_du_mouvement_non-permanent_des_eaux_avec_application_aux_crues_des_rivieres_et_a_lintroduction_des_marees_dans_leur_lit","312116185_The_constitution_and_properties_of_solids_and_liquids","305510054_Well-posedness_and_